<body>
<div class="wallpaper"></div>

<header>
    <div class="row"><div class="logo">Side Quest: Shark Gun Sprint</div><span class="badge">30–60 min</span></div>
    <nav>
        <a href="/">Dashboard</a>
        <a href="/coding.html">Coding</a>
        <a href="/modeling.html">3D Modeling</a>
        <a href="/tutorials.html">Tutorials</a>
        <a href="/library/">Assets</a>
        <a class="active" href="/sidequest-sharkgun.html">Side Quest</a>
    </nav>
</header>

<main class="grid">
    <section class="card" style="grid-column:span 12">
        <h2>Goal</h2>
        <p>Make a shark-themed item + sound and see it in-game today. Screenshot = win.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
        <h3>1) Pixel icon</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Create a 16×16 or 32×32 PNG for your Shark Gun icon (Piskel/Aseprite).</li>
            <li>Save in <code>/public/textures/</code>.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
        <h3>2) (Optional) 3D model</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Blockbench → simple gun model; texture it.</li>
            <li>Export JSON/PNG and add to your mod resources.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
        <h3>3) Sound</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Pick a SFX from <code>/public/sounds/sfx/</code> or record/edit in Audacity.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
        <h3>4) Wire it (Java)</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Register item (SharkGun), point to texture, play SFX on use.</li>
            <li>Run dev client → test → take a screenshot for the “Victory” folder.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</main>

<div class="toast" id="toast"></div>
<script src="/assets/js/site.js" defer></script>
</body>
</html>
